{
  "stem": "14463.1",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because you see, what happens is in Poland, before the war, the rabbis used to travel.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they traveled from city to city.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he was-- the Halbrarstam-- my grandfather was a great-- he used to donate a lot of money to that movement, to the [NON-ENGLISH] movement.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The rabbi was called the [NON-ENGLISH], because he came from a city called [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he used to donate that money.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So when he came to our city, he used to actually live in our place-- in my grandfather's place.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And there was such a commotion at that time that I can't even tell you because usually they all went to the synagogue together.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So the synagogue was packed to the rafters because the [NON-ENGLISH] has arrived.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "He was equivalent, as you would say now, to the Lubavitcher rabbi, but of course, with a smaller congregation.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But this is the authority he had.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And I remember very fondly that after Shabbos, after lunch-- you know, came home for lunch to my grandfather-- you couldn't go in.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "There was food on the tables.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "It was everything.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And my grandfather was sitting next to the rabbi.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And the rabbi was dispensing words of wisdom from the Torah.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And I used to sit on grandfather's knees.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And we each Chaim, from [NON-ENGLISH] or whatever it was there, by hand, with hand.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "I remember that as today.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And all my cousins were very jealous of me because I was the only one which was sitting on grandfather's knees next to the rabbi.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And the rabbi once even blessed me.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Very fondly.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I had a wonderful, you know, youth.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I mean, not youth, but childhood-- wonderful childhood.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Smothered in love and affection.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Smothered, from my mother, my father, my brother.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Because I was a little boychik.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
